-- в”Ђв”Ђ Phase 64 namespace type в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
--
-- Collision namespace holds pair-based 2D/3D collision tests that
-- have no single natural receiver (circle-circle, sphere-sphere,
-- line-line, point-circle). Natural-receiver collision methods
-- attach to Rectangle / Vector2 / Ray / BoundingBox directly.
object Collision {}

-- в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ
-- Textures & Images (Phase 66) вЂ” Color math (TEX-13, Plan 66-01)
-- в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ
--
-- 18 raylib Color-math functions (raylib.h:1437-1453) bound as idiomatic
-- Iron methods on the Color namespace. Every stub lowers to
-- Iron_color_<name>(...) in iron_raylib.c.
--
-- Return-by-value semantics: raylib's ColorFade/ColorTint/... all take
-- Color by value and return Color by value вЂ” Iron mirrors this exactly.
-- Users rebind: val faded = original.fade(0.5).
--
-- Receiver param names: c / other / tint / dst / src вЂ” NEVER `self`
-- (E0101 reserved). Phase 64-01 precedent.
--
-- Color.from_int takes UInt32 to exercise the primitive-arg path with
-- raylib's GetColor. Color.from_pixel_data / Color.to_pixel_data take
-- `data: Int` (Iron int64_t); the shim reinterprets via
-- (void *)(intptr_t)data. First opaque-pointer function argument in
-- the raylib binding.
--
-- PixelFormat enum is lowered to int32_t by the Phase 62 enum-cast
-- convention; the shim casts to raylib's `int` at the boundary.

func Color.is_equal(c: Color, other: Color) -> Bool {}
func Color.fade(c: Color, alpha: Float32) -> Color {}
func Color.to_int(c: Color) -> Int32 {}
func Color.normalize(c: Color) -> Vector4 {}
func Color.from_normalized(v: Vector4) -> Color {}
func Color.to_hsv(c: Color) -> Vector3 {}
func Color.from_hsv(hue: Float32, saturation: Float32, value: Float32) -> Color {}
func Color.tint(c: Color, tint: Color) -> Color {}
func Color.brightness(c: Color, factor: Float32) -> Color {}
func Color.contrast(c: Color, contrast: Float32) -> Color {}
func Color.alpha(c: Color, alpha: Float32) -> Color {}
func Color.alpha_blend(dst: Color, src: Color, tint: Color) -> Color {}
func Color.lerp(c: Color, other: Color, factor: Float32) -> Color {}
func Color.from_int(hex_value: UInt32) -> Color {}
func Color.from_pixel_data(data: Int, format: PixelFormat) -> Color {}
func Color.to_pixel_data(data: Int, c: Color, format: PixelFormat) {}
func Color.pixel_data_size(width: Int32, height: Int32, format: PixelFormat) -> Int32 {}

-- в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ
-- Image I/O + Generation + Extraction (Plan 66-02)
-- в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ
--
-- Closes TEX-01 (file-path load/unload/valid), narrowed TEX-02 (from
-- Texture / from Screen / animated-from-file), TEX-03 (9 procedural
-- generators), narrowed TEX-04 (file export), TEX-06 (colors / palette
-- / alpha border / pixel color).
--
-- Deferred to a follow-up phase (memory-buffer surface blocked by the
-- [UInt8] FFI gap per Phase 66 RESEARCH Pitfall 7):
--   LoadImageRaw, LoadImageFromMemory, LoadImageAnimFromMemory,
--   ExportImageToMemory.
--
-- Receiver naming: `img` for Image receivers, `tex` for Texture
-- receivers. Never `self` (E0101 reserved).
--
-- TEX-06 is the first reverse-direction `-> [Color]` in raylib.iron вЂ”
-- Task 1 probe confirmed GREEN (emit_structs.c:309-312 auto-emits
-- Iron_List_Iron_Color via the foreign-method-stub return scan).

-- Image load/unload/valid (TEX-01) + narrowed TEX-02
